parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat bracket can cause the seat to collapse, leading to an uneven and unsafe driving position, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The seat collapses or sags on one side
the seat height cannot be adjusted
the seat makes an audible noise or pop when moving
the seat bracket is broken or welded incorrectly
the seat cushion is no longer supported.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall Delays and Inconvenience
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed repair of the Takata airbag recall can cause inconvenience and safety risks to vehicle owners, as they are advised not to allow passengers to ride in the front passenger seat until the repair is completed.
symptoms: Long wait times for repair appointments
unavailability of parts
conflicting information from dealerships and manufacturers
and inconvenience due to not being able to use the front passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dealership Refusal to Perform Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dealerships' refusal to perform recall repairs can put vehicle owners at risk of safety hazards and accidents.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to perform recall repairs
citing unreasonable conditions or requirements
and vehicle owners being unable to get their vehicles repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Communication and Transparency from Manufacturers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of communication and transparency from manufacturers can cause frustration and anxiety for vehicle owners, making it difficult for them to get their vehicles repaired.
symptoms: Vehicle owners not receiving recall notifications
lack of information on the status of recall repairs
and conflicting information from dealerships and manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to longer stopping distances and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Brake warning light comes on
brake fluid leakage
soft or spongy brake pedal
reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature rear brake wear can cause reduced braking performance, leading to longer stopping distances and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Rear brake pads and rotors wear out quickly
grinding or scraping noise from the rear brakes
vibration when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system malfunction can cause loss of braking control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: ABS system engages unnecessarily
loss of braking control
wheels lock up
vehicle skids or slides.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Concentric slave cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
